        <page n="01" image="va.au.ss.1857.06.24.01">
            <div type="l">
                <column>7</column>
                <head>For the Spectator; Bath Alum Springs, June 18, 1857</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>W.</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>Letter extolling the virtues of Virginia's Mineral Springs, emphasizing
                    their accesibility to both sections of the country.</summary>
            </div>
            <pageNote/>
        </page>
        <page n="02" image="va.au.ss.1857.06.24.02">
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Intense Excitement</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Eckle</ln>
                        <pf>Peter</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>McGruder</ln>
                        <fn>Margaret</fn>
                        <pf>Mrs.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Flaig</ln>
                        <pf>Mr.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Wygand</ln>
                        <pf>Martin</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Staunton swept by a rumor that a grave had been discovered inside a vacant
                    house. Actually, it was just a bundle of smelly old clothes in a
                cellar.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Visit to Mossy Creek</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>Never do we take an excursion to the country without finding something new
                    to admire in our delightful Valley of Virginia.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Hotchkiss</ln>
                        <pf>Mr.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Brodt</ln>
                        <pf>Mr.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Boler</ln>
                        <pf>Jacob G.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Gray</ln>
                        <pf>R. A.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>SS editors visited Mossy Creek and attended commencement exercises at Mossy
                    Creek Academy. The school had over 100 pupils last term.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>The Circuit Court</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Circuit Court finished its session, which began on 6/1/57. Article contains
                    omplaints about lawyers tendency to make loud, overlong speeches.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>"Thoroughly Organized"</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The Institution for the Deaf Dumb and Blind has received a new organ from
                    New York. Blind students are taught to play so that they can support
                themselves.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>High Prices</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>SS is clarifying its editorial complaining about high prices. It blames
                    speculators, not the farmers themselves.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Augusta Fire Association</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>It is well enough for persons who wish to enjoy the "4th" to make
                    arrangements for leaving Staunton on that day--There does not seem to be
                    patriotism ebough left about here to get up any kind of a celebration.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The Fire Association is planning a 4th of July picnic and excursion to
                    Craigsville.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>June Court</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Court approved $700 to pay for the renovation of the court house.</summary>
            </div>
            <pageNote/>
        </page>
